.TH SSHFLING 1 "July 2026" "sshfling 0.1.24" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
sshfling \- grant and revoke temporary SSH access
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B sshfling
[\fB--json\fR] [\fB--version\fR]
[\fBsetup\fR]
[\fB-t\fR \fIDURATION\fR]
[\fB--username\fR \fINAME\fR]
[\fB--password\fR|\fB--certificate\fR]
.br
.B sshfling
\fBdoctor\fR [\fB--dependencies\fR]
.br
.B sshfling
\fBshutdown\fR [\fIUSERNAME\fR]
.br
.B sshfling
\fBlist\fR
.br
.B sshfling
\fBpassword prune\fR [\fB--all\fR]
.br
.B sshfling
\fBcert issue\fR [\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.br
.B sshfling
\fBhost install\fR [\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.br
.B sshfling
\fBserve\fR [\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B sshfling
creates short-lived SSH access grants. It can create temporary password grants,
issue OpenSSH user certificates, install host policy, run an issuer service,
and revoke or list active sessions.
.PP
Access lifetime, connection count, and access-level limits are enforced by the
project policy file and forced-session wrapper on configured hosts.
.SH COMMON COMMANDS
.TP
.B doctor
Check local tools and deployment files. Use
.B --dependencies
to report dependency state.
.TP
.B setup
Create temporary SSH access. Password access is the default; use
.B --certificate
to issue a certificate instead.
.TP
.B shutdown
Kill active SSHFling SSH sessions.
.TP
.B list
List active SSHFling SSH sessions.
.TP
.B password prune
Remove expired temporary password grants.
.TP
.B cert issue
Sign a public key for temporary SSH access.
.TP
.B host install
Configure a production SSH host to trust the SSHFling CA and forced-session
wrapper.
.TP
.B serve
Run the temporary SSH certificate issuer service.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B --json
Emit stable JSON where supported.
.TP
.B --version
Print the installed version.
.TP
.BI "-t, --time " DURATION
Set the access lifetime, for example
.BR 30s ,
.BR 5m ,
.BR 1h ,
or
.BR 24h .
.TP
.BI "--username " NAME
Set the temporary SSH username.
.TP
.B --password
Create temporary password SSH access.
.TP
.B --certificate
Create temporary certificate SSH access.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/sshfling/policy.json
Host policy file.
.TP
.I /etc/sshfling/sshflingd.env
Issuer service environment file. This file may contain secrets and is installed
with restricted permissions.
.TP
.I /var/lib/sshflingd
Service state directory for the packaged issuer service.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.B sshfling
exits with status 0 on success and non-zero on validation, dependency, or
runtime errors.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR ssh (1),
.BR ssh-keygen (1),
.BR sshd_config (5),
.BR systemd.service (5)
